title: Huskerland Top Tens: Classes A, B
text: 9. Papillion-LaVista 4-310. Kearney 5-2 Bob Sez: Bellevue West holds off Millard North, 35-28, but with Grand Island losing to 3-4 Millard South, 13-10, we still move the Mustangs up a spot to No. 3. Millard West rolled North Platte, 42-7, while Central remains unbeaten (49-6 over Bellevue East) and Norfolk comes back after the Millard West loss to win, but only barely, beating 4-3 Lincoln Northeast 35-33. Papio South (48-0 over Omaha Northwest) and Westside (55-14 over Columbus) won easily while Papillion-LaVista (21-6 over Lincoln North Star) and Kearney (42-3 over Omaha Bryan) also won. Top Games for Week 8: Papillion-LaVista South at Millard North (Thursday), Millard West at Kearney, Norfolk at North Platte, Bellevue West at Creighton Prep, Omaha Westside at Omaha North, Grand Island at Lincoln Northeast. Class B
